summary: This is an email from the FBI's dropbox system indicating the upload of an XML file related to Jeffrey Epstein and child sex trafficking. It serves as a record of file transfer within the FBI network.

events.title: FBI Upload of Epstein Case File
events.description: An XML file titled 'Epstein_Jeffrey_Child_Sex_Trafficking_-.xml' was uploaded via the FBI's dropbox system from FBINET to UNET.

keyFacts: An FBI email dated July 5, 2019, documents the transfer of a file related to Jeffrey Epstein and child sex trafficking.
The file was an XML document with the name 'Epstein_Jeffrey_Child_Sex_Trafficking_-.xml'.
The transfer occurred from FBINET to UNET, indicating internal FBI network communication.
The document is a metadata record of a file upload, not the substantive case file itself.
